## Frontend dev proxy targets (optional)
## If your backends aren't on the default ports, set these in `.env` (not committed).
##
## Examples:
## VOICE_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8010
## GESTURE_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000
##
## If you are running Vite in WSL but the Python backends on Windows,
## point these to your Windows host IP (e.g. http://192.168.1.10:8000).
#
# VOICE_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8010
# GESTURE_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000

## HTTPS dev server (recommended for mobile testing)
## Default is true; set to false if you explicitly need plain HTTP.
# VITE_HTTPS=true

## Optional: use your own trusted HTTPS cert (recommended if you want the browser to show "Secure").
## Example (mkcert): VITE_SSL_CERT_PATH=certs/localhost.pem, VITE_SSL_KEY_PATH=certs/localhost-key.pem
# VITE_SSL_CERT_PATH=
# VITE_SSL_KEY_PATH=
